 {"id":"frankenredis-cz1u","title":"redis parity: ACL LOG should preserve MULTI context for queued authorization failures","description":"Upstream redis/tests/unit/acl.tcl expects ACL LOG context=multi when an ACL denial happens inside MULTI/EXEC. Local ServerState::record_acl_log_event in crates/fr-runtime/src/lib.rs currently hardcodes context='toplevel', so queued transaction denials lose their Redis context. Thread the MULTI execution context through ACL logging and keep object/client-info parity with Redis.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:53:37.145801001Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T17:25:14.063758374Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T17:25:14.061044326Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
